'''Willian Joel Pacho Tenorio''' (born 16 October 2001) is an Ecuadorian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defender (association football)|centre-back]] for [[Ligue 1]] club [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] and the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]].<ref>{{cite web |publisher=Royal Antwerp F.C. |url=https://royalantwerpfc.be/nieuws/willianpacho |title=Willian Pacho moves to Eintracht Frankfurt |date=30 March 2023 |access-date=30 March 2023 |language=nl}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Independiente del Valle===

From [[Quinindé]] in the far north of Ecuador, Pacho moved to the suburbs of capital [[Quito]] to debut with [[Independiente del Valle]] in 2019, with both he and the club going on to enjoy a remarkable run of success over the next three years.

A non-playing substitute across the entire [[2018 U-20 Copa Libertadores]] run that saw IDV reach the final only to lose to 2–1 in the decider to Uruguayans [[Club Nacional de Football|Nacional]],<ref>{{cite web |publisher=[[Conmebol]] |url=https://www.conmebol.com/noticias/nacional-de-uruguay-campeon/ |title=¡Nacional de Uruguay campeón! |date=24 February 2018 |access-date=30 March 2023 |language=es|trans-title=Nacional de Uruguay champions!}}</ref> Pacho was first named on the bench for IDV's 2–0 win at [[Mushuc Runa S.C.|Mushuc Runa]] on 15 March 2019.<ref>{{cite web |publisher=[[El Universo]] |url=https://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/2019/03/15/nota/7234676/vivo-mushuc-runa-vs-independiente-valle-fecha-6-ecuador-liga-pro/ |title=Mushuc Runa 0–2 Independiente del Valle |date=15 March 2019 |access-date=30 March 2023 |language=es}}</ref>

Pacho was finally given his first-team debut in November of that year, starting in the 0–0 draw against [[Delfín S.C.|Delfin]]<ref>{{cite web |publisher=flashscore.com |url=https://www.flashscore.com/match/KtBVRvRj/#/match-summary/lineups/ |title=Flash Score: Independiente del Valle 0–0 Delfin |date=2 November 2019 |access-date=30 March 2023 |language=en}}</ref> that rounded off IDV's regular season campaign ahead of the [[2019 Ecuadorian Serie A|Ecuadorian League Play-Offs]], the match coming a week before Independiente del Valle claimed their first ever international crown, beating [[Club Atlético Colón|Colón]] of Argentina 3–1 in [[Asunción]] in the [[2019 Copa Sudamericana Final]].<ref>{{cite web |publisher=[[Diario AS]] |url=https://colombia.as.com/colombia/2019/11/10/futbol/1573343443_803119.html |title=Dájome and Independiente, South American champions |date=9 November 2019 |access-date=30 March 2023 |language=es}}</ref> Pacho was not a member of the continental squad, but did feature heavily in IDV's [[2020 U-20 Copa Libertadores]] triumph, playing all but one game.

Independiente beat [[Clube de Regatas do Flamengo|Flamengo]] of Brazil on penalties in the semi-finals, and Argentine giants [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]] 2–1 in the final in [[Luque]]. Pacho started both knockout games in defence. With a good young crop coming through, Independiente del Valle went on to lift the Ecuadorian League title for the very first time in 2021, defeating [[Club Sport Emelec|Emelec]] in the finals by a 4–2 aggregate score. Pacho played 17 games on the road to glory, starting when he was 16.

===Royal Antwerp===

Having been spotted by Belgian scouts, Pacho signed a five-year contract with title-chasing [[Royal Antwerp F.C.|Royal Antwerp]] on 28 January 2022.<ref>{{cite web |publisher=[[Royal Antwerp F.C.|Royal Antwerp FC]] |url=https://royalantwerpfc.be/nieuws/william-pacho-tekent-op-de-bosuil |title=William Pacho Tekent Op De Bosuil! |date=28 January 2022 |access-date=8 February 2022 |language=nl|trans-title=William Pacho Signs At De Bosuil!}}</ref> Pacho only played three league games in his first season with Antwerp for coach [[Brian Priske]], as the Great Old finished fourth in the Belgian League title play-offs behind champions [[Club Brugge]], runners-up [[Royale Union Saint-Gilloise]] and third-placed [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]], who beat Antwerp home and away in the Championship play-offs to keep the Great Old at bay.

Under new coach [[Mark van Bommel]], Pacho became a fixture in the Royal Antwerp defence for the 2022–23 season, as Antwerp won their first nine games of the season on the way to qualifying for the [[2023 Belgian Cup Final]] and [[2022–23 Belgian Pro League|title play-offs]], and within months had attracted interest from [[Ligue 1]], the [[Scottish Premiership]] and [[Bundesliga]]. An agreement was reached during the winter transfer window in January 2023 between Royal Antwerp and reigning [[UEFA Europa League]] champions [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] that Pacho would join them at the end of the season.

Pacho started Antwerp's [[2023 Belgian Cup Final]] win over [[KV Mechelen|Mechelen]], the club's second triumph in the competition in four seasons.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Geen schoonheidsprijs, wel een vierde beker: Antwerp maakt favorietenrol waar tegen KV Mechelen |url=https://sporza.be/nl/matches/voetbal/croky-cup/2022-2023/finale/01/kv-mechelen-antwerp-geen-schoonheidsprijs-wel-een-vierde-beker-antwerp-maakt-favorietenrol-waar-tegen-kv-mechelen~1664288888029/ |date=30 April 2023 |website=Sporza |language=nl|trans-title=No beauty prize, but a fourth cup: Antwerp fulfills the role of favourite against KV Mechelen}}</ref>

===Eintracht Frankfurt===

On 30 March 2023, it was announced that Pacho had signed a five-year contract with Eintracht, valid from 1 June.<ref>{{cite web |date=30 March 2023 |title=Willian Pacho wechselt zu Eintracht Frankfurt |url=https://profis.eintracht.de/news/willian-pacho-wechselt-zu-eintracht-frankfurt-149419 |access-date=30 March 2023 |publisher=[[Eintracht Frankfurt]] |language=de|trans-title=Willian Pacho moves to Eintracht Frankfurt}}</ref> In the 2023–24 season, Pacho started in 42 matches in all competitions, ranking among [[Eintracht Frankfurt]]'s best players for duels won and passes completed.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/willian-pacho-who-is-eintracht-frankfurt-ecuador-defender-26106 |title=Willian Pacho: Who is the Eintracht Frankfurt and Ecuador central defender? |publisher=Bundesliga |date=1 August 2024}}</ref>

===Paris Saint-Germain===

On 9 August 2024, it was announced Pacho had officially signed for [[Ligue 1]] club [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] (PSG) for a reported upfront fee of €40 million (potentially rising to €45 million) on a five-year contract deal.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Willian |first=Pacho |date=7 August 2024 |title=Willian Pacho to undergo PSG medical |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/willian-pacho-psg-done-deal-143700276.html |access-date=25 April 2026 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en-US}}</ref> He became the club's first Ecuadorian player.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Willian Pacho signs for Paris Saint-Germain until 2029 |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/willian-pacho-signs-for-paris-saint-germain-until-2029-psg-mercato-2425-saison-reprise-2024-2025 |access-date=25 April 2026 |website=Paris Saint-Germain F.C. |language=en}}</ref> On 16 August, Pacho made his official debut for PSG in a 4–1 victory over [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Première pour Willian Pacho |url=https://www.psg.fr/equipes/equipe-premiere/content/premiere-pour-willian-pacho-le-havre-ac-paris-saint-germain-ligue-1-20242025 |access-date=25 April 2026 |website=Paris Saint-Germain F.C. |language=en}}</ref>

On 31 May 2025, he started  in a 5–0 victory over [[Inter Milan]] in the [[2025 UEFA Champions League final|Champions League final]], becoming the first Ecuadorian to win the competition, and the fourth to win an UEFA competition, after [[Antonio Valencia]], [[Pervis Estupiñán]] and [[Moisés Caicedo]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Willian Pacho, first Ecuadorian to win the Champions League |url=https://copaamerica.com/en/news/willian-pacho-ecuadorian-champions-league-winner-2025 |access-date=25 April 2026 |website=copaamerica.com}}</ref> He scored his first goal for PSG, which was also his first career club goal, on 21 October 2025 during the 7–2 victory against [[Bundesliga]] club [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] in the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League league phase|UEFA Champions League league phase]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Filip |first=Holender |date=7 August 2024 |title=88CLB |url=https://88clbvietnam.com/ |access-date=25 April 2026 |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=Leverkusen vs Paris: UEFA Champions League 2025/26 League phase |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2045941--leverkusen-vs-paris/ |access-date=25 April 2026 |website=UEFA.com |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
Pacho was included in the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador senior squad]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], but did not play in any match.<ref>{{Cite web |title=FIFA World Cup Qatar 2022 {{!}} Squad list: Ecuador (ECU) |url=https://fdp.fifa.org/assetspublic/ce44/pdf/SquadLists-English.pdf|publisher=[[FIFA]] |page=10 |date=15 November 2022 |access-date=15 November 2022}}</ref> He debuted on 28 March 2023 in a 2–1 friendly victory against [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia]] in [[Melbourne]] while scoring his first international goal.<ref>{{Cite news |title=William Pacho: debut, gol y triunfo tricolor |url=https://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/futbol/william-pacho-debut-gol-y-triunfo-tricolor-nota/ |website=[[El Universo]] |date=28 March 2023 |language=es}}</ref>

Pacho was called up to the final 26-man Ecuador squad for the [[2024 Copa América]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/futbol/ecuador-presenta-lista-oficial-para-la-copa-america-gonzalo-plata-y-robert-arboleda-quedaron-relegados-nota/|title=Ecuador presenta lista oficial para la Copa América: Gonzalo Plata y Robert Arboleda quedaron relegados|trans-title=Ecuador presents official roster for Copa America: Gonzalo Plata and Robert Arboleda left off the list|publisher=[[El Universo]]|date=29 May 2024|language=es}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Pacho's first name is often mistakenly listed as "William", since the two are almost interchangeably used in Spanish.<ref name="Gael 2022">{{cite web |last=Gael |first=Hannes Van |title=Willian (met 'n') Pacho steelt met de ogen van Alderweireld en is certitude bij Antwerp: "Gelukkig kan Mark van Bommel het heel goed uitleggen in het Spaans" |website=Gazet van Antwerpen |date=24 December 2022 |url=https://www.gva.be/cnt/dmf20221223_97274632 |language=nl |access-date=30 March 2023|trans-title=Willian (with an 'n') Pacho learns with his eyes from Alderweireld and is a fixture at Antwerp: "Fortunately, Mark van Bommel can explain things very well in Spanish"}}</ref>

